                <p class="questions">
                    Define a GEM. What is their use for the production of vaccines?
                </p>
                <div class="collapseContentDisabled">
                    <p>
                        A GEM is defined as a genetically engineered microorganism. A GEM is in principle the same as a GMO; genetically modified organism.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The goals remain more or less the same:
                    </p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            Amplify or modify genes that code for interesting metabolic enzymes.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Minimise metabolic dead ends.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Increase efficiency and production of energy.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Add heterologous genes that may give new metabolic properties.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <p>
                        There are some downsides when creating GMOs/GEMs:
                    </p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            The manipulations we apply may reduce fitness of the organism.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            There may be an imbalance or increase in energy consumption; we may inadvetently make the organism less efficient because of the increase in genetic material.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            There is a risk that the modifications may spread to other wild organisms.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <p>
                        This is why the development of a suicide-GMO/GEM is important, as if it were to get out into the wild it should not be able to live on its own without our artificial environements. A way of doing this classically is making the organism auxotrophic for something we provide in the lab.
                    </p>
